Here's how to implement all three requirements:

### 1. Custom "Cancel" Back Button (in `EditProductPage.xaml`)

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.EditProductPage">

    <Shell.BackButtonBehavior>
        <BackButtonBehavior TextOverride="Cancel"
                            Command="{Binding BackCommand}" />
    </Shell.BackButtonBehavior>

    <!-- your form content -->
</ContentPage>
```

### 2. Navigation Guard (in `AppShell.xaml.cs`)

Use `OnNavigating` with `GetDeferral()` to intercept back navigation, show a dialog, and cancel if the user wants to stay:

```csharp
protected override async void OnNavigating(ShellNavigatingEventArgs args)
{
    base.OnNavigating(args);

    // Only intercept back (Pop) navigation from EditProductPage
    if (args.Source == ShellNavigationSource.Pop
        && Shell.Current.CurrentPage is EditProductPage page
        && page.HasUnsavedChanges)
    {
        var deferral = args.GetDeferral();

        bool discard = await Shell.Current.CurrentPage.DisplayAlert(
            "Unsaved Changes",
            "You have unsaved changes. Discard them?",
            "Discard", "Stay");

        if (!discard)
            args.Cancel();

        deferral.Complete();
    }
}
```

### 3. ViewModel BackCommand & HasUnsavedChanges

```csharp
// EditProductPage.xaml.cs
public bool HasUnsavedChanges { get; set; }

// ViewModel
public ICommand BackCommand => new Command(async () =>
{
    // This triggers OnNavigating, which handles the guard
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync("..");
});
```

**Key points:**
- `GetDeferral()` is required because `DisplayAlert` is async â€” without it, navigation completes before the dialog returns.
- `args.Cancel()` stops navigation when the user taps "Stay."
- `TextOverride="Cancel"` replaces the default back arrow with "Cancel" text.
- The `BackCommand` on `BackButtonBehavior` ensures tapping the custom button also goes through the same guard.
